1
00:00:18,070 --> 00:00:20,116
- Thought you'd gone home.
- I wish. We're up.

2
00:00:20,241 --> 00:00:23,147
A double homicide in Rancho Rosa.
Local sheriff's in over his head.

3
00:00:23,315 --> 00:00:24,821
- I'm on it.
- Boss,

4
00:00:25,317 --> 00:00:27,443
you've been promising me
more time in the field.

5
00:00:27,611 --> 00:00:28,944
Now's as good a time as any.

6
00:00:29,806 --> 00:00:32,323
You're right.
Be a cover in the office on this one.

7
00:00:32,697 --> 00:00:33,574
Let's go.

8
00:00:36,534 --> 00:00:38,871
- You're okay with this, I hope?
- Absolutely.

9
00:00:52,556 --> 00:00:53,682
What's going on?

10
00:00:53,807 --> 00:00:56,360
Looks like two bullets
to the chest for each of them.

11
00:00:56,485 --> 00:00:58,987
Freshness of the wounds
suggest it happened recently.

12
00:00:59,112 --> 00:01:01,061
Selby and Jana Vickers, 33

13
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:03,825
and 31 years old,
from here in Rancho Rosa.

14
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:06,094
Identify
from their driver's licenses.

15
00:01:06,389 --> 00:01:08,848
- Who found the bodies?
- Couple of teenagers.

16
00:01:08,973 --> 00:01:12,403
This place is a local lover's lane.
Apparently, thieves know that, too.

17
00:01:12,966 --> 00:01:14,865
Sheriff thinks
that it's a robbery gone sour.

18
00:01:15,629 --> 00:01:17,159
Little old to be necking, no?

19
00:01:17,935 --> 00:01:19,286
There's an age limit on that?

20
00:01:19,981 --> 00:01:22,277
Plus their clothes aren't,
disheveled.

21
00:01:23,306 --> 00:01:24,356
Good point.

22
00:01:24,897 --> 00:01:27,044
There's a little white thing there,

23
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:28,951
sticking out from Jana's dress.

24
00:01:29,721 --> 00:01:31,510
Could you...
Yeah that's it.

25
00:01:34,222 --> 00:01:35,261
$800 dress.

26
00:01:37,132 --> 00:01:39,432
Is that a useful "aha"
or an irritating "aha"?

27
00:01:41,205 --> 00:01:44,015
The borrowed dress tells us
they were going somewhere fancy

28
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:46,981
and wanted to make an impression.
Not usually something they'd go for,

29
00:01:47,149 --> 00:01:49,608
or they'd have a later model car.

30
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,418
He needed a few pulls on the scotch
just to take the edge off

31
00:01:53,906 --> 00:01:56,239
because he was nervous
about who was gonna be there,

32
00:01:56,364 --> 00:01:58,843
which in a small town like this,
likely means

33
00:01:59,068 --> 00:02:01,052
relatives or people from his past.

34
00:02:02,563 --> 00:02:04,331
Wedding, maybe?
Or birthday party?

35
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:07,001
- No gift, which leaves...
- No guessing games.

36
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:09,837
Excuse me, sheriff?

37
00:02:10,499 --> 00:02:12,548
What's the name
of the local high school?

38
00:02:20,553 --> 00:02:21,553
Stephanie?

39
00:02:23,599 --> 00:02:24,769
You look fantastic.

40
00:02:25,297 --> 00:02:26,771
I'm sorry.
I'm not Stephanie.

41
00:02:30,212 --> 00:02:31,859
Do that again, and I'll arrest you.

42
00:02:32,264 --> 00:02:35,016
Sorry, I had to.
You've always been the one.

43
00:02:40,709 --> 00:02:42,028
I'm not the one.

44
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:53,280
High school.

45
00:02:53,456 --> 00:02:55,156
Best years of your life.

46
00:03:07,452 --> 00:03:08,354


47
00:03:10,554 --> 00:03:12,191
Welcome back to Rancho Rosa High.

48
00:03:12,656 --> 00:03:13,656
Go, Toros!

49
00:03:14,314 --> 00:03:17,380
I'm Tess. One of your student
ambassadors this weekend.

50
00:03:17,505 --> 00:03:19,355
Nametags and reunion books.

51
00:03:19,992 --> 00:03:22,417
We're with the California
Bureau of Investigation.

52
00:03:23,199 --> 00:03:25,509
We need to know
if Jana and Selby Vickers

53
00:03:25,634 --> 00:03:27,039
were expected here tonight.

54
00:03:30,041 --> 00:03:32,141
Selby Vickers and his wife Jana.

55
00:03:32,631 --> 00:03:34,590
They also replied "yes"
to tomorrow's

56
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:37,341
homecoming picnic and dance.
Is everything okay?

57
00:03:37,924 --> 00:03:40,344
We need to talk to somebody
who would know them.

58
00:03:43,137 --> 00:03:44,098
Redheaded woman.

59
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:47,101
That's Willa Brock.
She's the reunion committee chair.

60
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:50,229
You really think we were young enough
to be in this class, did you?

61
00:03:51,258 --> 00:03:54,024
Everyone over the age of 21
looks the same to me.

62
00:03:54,330 --> 00:03:57,238
Tactful and evasive.
You're gonna do very well in life, Tess.

63
00:03:57,363 --> 00:03:58,195
Go, Toros.

64
00:04:00,770 --> 00:04:01,870
I'm stunned.

65
00:04:02,735 --> 00:04:05,588
It was surprising enough
Selby was even coming.

66
00:04:05,713 --> 00:04:07,715
- Now this?
- Why the surprise?

67
00:04:08,397 --> 00:04:10,541
Well, he wasn't
at the fifth or the tenth.

68
00:04:11,807 --> 00:04:12,695
Because...

69
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:15,921
Because he was expelled
and never graduated.

70
00:04:16,968 --> 00:04:19,571
Selby pulled this...
It was a really nasty prank.

71
00:04:19,696 --> 00:04:22,190
What was it, senior year?
It was his one and only.

72
00:04:22,315 --> 00:04:24,847
Vice principal Desouza caught him,
gave him the ol'boot.

73
00:04:25,085 --> 00:04:27,600
- What was the prank?
- There was this,

74
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:30,728
shall we say,
socially challenged boy

75
00:04:30,853 --> 00:04:33,314
- named Derek Logan.
- Selby dragged him

76
00:04:33,482 --> 00:04:35,415
into the girls' locker room,
he blindfolded him

77
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:38,167
with his own underwear,
tied him up, naked,

78
00:04:39,068 --> 00:04:42,072
took his picture and then
posted it all over the school.

79
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:45,268
- How sick is that, right?
- It was disturbing.

80
00:04:47,177 --> 00:04:49,498
Is there anything else
you can tell us about him?

81
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:50,873
I played football...

82
00:04:51,058 --> 00:04:53,226
Starting running back.
People are still talking

83
00:04:53,351 --> 00:04:55,586
about the 5 touchdowns
I scored against Stratton.

84
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:57,784
What does
that have to do with Selby?

85
00:04:58,132 --> 00:04:59,131
I was popular.

86
00:04:59,696 --> 00:05:01,746
I was a jock.
He was a nobody.

87
00:05:02,198 --> 00:05:04,245
I don't know
what kind of person he was.

88
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:06,764
How about his current life?

89
00:05:07,095 --> 00:05:08,858
<i>I got nada.
I got out of this town</i>

90
00:05:08,983 --> 00:05:11,226
as fast as I could.
I live down in Newport Beach now.

91
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:16,398
How about you, Willa?
Have you heard anything about Selby?

92
00:05:17,622 --> 00:05:19,878
I host a daytime
talk show in Chicago

93
00:05:20,003 --> 00:05:23,094
that tapes two shows a day
and is about to go national.

94
00:05:23,219 --> 00:05:25,783
I'm lucky if I hear anything
about my own family.

95
00:05:26,613 --> 00:05:29,191
Derek Logan. That kid
that Selby pulled the prank on.

96
00:05:29,316 --> 00:05:30,930
Could you point him out to us?

97
00:05:31,248 --> 00:05:33,040
Derek Logan?
He's not here?

98
00:05:33,890 --> 00:05:35,287
- No way!
- Gabe,

99
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:37,294
So good to see you again.

100
00:05:39,285 --> 00:05:40,536
You almost didn't.

101
00:05:40,818 --> 00:05:42,883
5 hours I spent
on the 101 driving here.

102
00:05:43,115 --> 00:05:45,886
CBI agent Teresa Lisbon,
Patrick Jane,

103
00:05:46,196 --> 00:05:47,638
- this is Gabe Nyland.
- Hi.

104
00:05:47,935 --> 00:05:49,735
D.A. for San Diego County.

105
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:51,710
You've prosecuted
a couple of cases for us.

106
00:05:51,835 --> 00:05:53,978
Now candidate
for Lieutenant Governor of California.

107
00:05:54,457 --> 00:05:55,637
Give me the word "g,"

108
00:05:55,762 --> 00:05:58,098
I start twisting arms for you
on election day, huh?

109
00:06:00,187 --> 00:06:02,444
Selby Vickers and his wife
were found murdered

110
00:06:02,711 --> 00:06:05,224
at the glen... Shot in their car.

111
00:06:06,225 --> 00:06:07,134
My god.

112
00:06:07,749 --> 00:06:10,308
I hadn't even heard that name
in 15 years till tonight.

113
00:06:10,897 --> 00:06:13,372
- Who did this?
- It's early in the investigation.

114
00:06:14,087 --> 00:06:15,683
You just got here, right?

115
00:06:16,443 --> 00:06:19,253
So how is it that you knew
Derek Logan wasn't here?

116
00:06:19,896 --> 00:06:21,892
Derek left the school
and moved out of state

117
00:06:22,017 --> 00:06:25,092
after that prank Selby pulled.
Word is he killed himself.

118
00:06:25,758 --> 00:06:26,857
Are you serious?

119
00:06:26,982 --> 00:06:29,013
I heard he was a blackjack dealer
at a casino.

120
00:06:29,443 --> 00:06:31,150
We'd like to talk to some classmates

121
00:06:31,275 --> 00:06:34,351
that still live in the area.
Maybe they know something about Selby.

122
00:06:34,638 --> 00:06:37,657
There are only a few,
but, the student ambassadors

123
00:06:37,896 --> 00:06:40,107
can probably point you
in the right direction.

124
00:06:40,536 --> 00:06:41,950
Thank you for your time.

125
00:06:46,448 --> 00:06:49,912
Nothing jumps out on this,
I'm gonna have the tech guys see it.

126
00:06:50,037 --> 00:06:52,043
Mail's all big bills
and small bank accounts.

127
00:06:52,168 --> 00:06:54,413
They certainly weren't
living the high life here.

128
00:06:55,263 --> 00:06:57,090
They didn't need to.
This was home.

129
00:06:57,215 --> 00:06:58,515
They were happy.

130
00:07:03,019 --> 00:07:05,424
<i>So I got you next
of kin info on Selby.</i>

131
00:07:06,173 --> 00:07:08,969
Mother in Rancho Rosa.
No luck on Jana, though.

132
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,675
<i>- Thanks. Text me the address?
- Will do.</i>

133
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:15,017
So I've never been
to Rancho Rosa before. What's it like?

134
00:07:15,265 --> 00:07:17,015
Nothing special. A town.

135
00:07:18,037 --> 00:07:20,230
Cool. What are you guys doing now?

136
00:07:21,021 --> 00:07:22,721
You know, investigating.

137
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:24,401
Come here.
Check this out.

138
00:07:24,841 --> 00:07:25,694
I gotta go.

139
00:07:26,474 --> 00:07:28,073
I'm busy... too.

140
00:07:37,431 --> 00:07:39,001
This is from yesterday morning.

141
00:07:40,475 --> 00:07:42,336
<i>I'm done playing games here.
You hear me?</i>

142
00:07:43,078 --> 00:07:45,798
<i>Either you get me my money,
or I'm gonna be forced to take action. </i>

143
00:07:46,853 --> 00:07:48,254
So much for happiness.

144
00:07:51,024 --> 00:07:54,071
So you haven't seen Selby
once in all these years?

145
00:07:54,196 --> 00:07:56,110
Supermarket, movie theater maybe?

146
00:07:57,339 --> 00:07:59,520
I mean, if I did, I don't remember.

147
00:07:59,977 --> 00:08:01,423
Hard to believe you, Stu.

148
00:08:02,344 --> 00:08:03,107
Sorry?

149
00:08:04,668 --> 00:08:05,609
Really? Okay.

150
00:08:06,182 --> 00:08:08,366
The hair plugs, the heels, this,

151
00:08:09,512 --> 00:08:10,948
professional woman here

152
00:08:11,116 --> 00:08:13,777
- posing as your girlfriend.
- Wait. What did you just say?

153
00:08:14,170 --> 00:08:16,028
Did he just call me...
What did he say...

154
00:08:16,328 --> 00:08:19,298
- That's all we need for your time...
- Beg my pardon.

155
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,827
- That's all we have. Thank you.
- I think you look lovely.

156
00:08:22,952 --> 00:08:25,252
- Have a good evening.
- Go, Toros.

157
00:08:27,863 --> 00:08:29,143
What's your problem?

158
00:08:30,841 --> 00:08:33,557
It's just a room
full of people lying to each other.

159
00:08:34,226 --> 00:08:37,151
Everyone here is trying so hard
to show how much they've changed,

160
00:08:37,276 --> 00:08:38,600
when the mere effort

161
00:08:39,308 --> 00:08:42,111
- screams that they haven't.
- Or they actually do change,

162
00:08:42,236 --> 00:08:45,136
with exceptions like
"Mr. Hair plugs", of course.

163
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:49,653
You got the rebel
who took the bank job,

164
00:08:50,441 --> 00:08:52,496
the player that stays
faithful to his wife.

165
00:08:52,621 --> 00:08:53,949
The rebel took the bank job

166
00:08:54,117 --> 00:08:56,425
because she sees
her rebellion is fruitless.

167
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:58,659
The player stays faithful
to his wife

168
00:08:58,784 --> 00:09:01,656
because the consequence
of infidelity is much greater now.

169
00:09:02,259 --> 00:09:03,333
But their instincts.

170
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:05,451
Their instincts never change.

171
00:09:05,576 --> 00:09:07,462
I'm a far cry from
what I was in high school.

172
00:09:08,064 --> 00:09:09,615
I wouldn't be so sure.

173
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:12,316
Driven to succeed to the point
of developing an ulcer,

174
00:09:12,441 --> 00:09:15,604
no tolerance for superiors
less sharp than yourself,

175
00:09:15,729 --> 00:09:17,957
shutting out girls
that wanted to hang out with you,

176
00:09:18,082 --> 00:09:20,027
blowing off boys
that want to get close...

177
00:09:20,152 --> 00:09:23,340
All the while,
at every turn, wondering,

178
00:09:23,465 --> 00:09:25,315
"what is it I really want?"

179
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:29,185
And you played an instrument.
My guess?

180
00:09:30,959 --> 00:09:32,959
- Clarinet.
- Not even close.

181
00:09:33,084 --> 00:09:35,936
I'll get the guest list to Rigsby.
I'll have him check everybody out.

182
00:09:36,061 --> 00:09:38,368
Have him locate
the whereabouts of Derek Logan.

183
00:09:39,151 --> 00:09:41,984
You really think logan laid
in wait for 15 years

184
00:09:42,109 --> 00:09:44,458
and suddenly decided
to take revenge on Selby?

185
00:09:45,514 --> 00:09:48,612
Well, I think that Logan
is as angry today

186
00:09:48,737 --> 00:09:51,996
as he was 15 years ago,
maybe even angrier.

187
00:09:52,384 --> 00:09:54,582
- We'll check him out.
- I'm gonna stick around.

188
00:09:54,707 --> 00:09:57,397
I didn't go to high school.
This is kind of fascinating for me.

189
00:09:57,522 --> 00:09:59,675
- You never went to high school?
- No, I was busy.

190
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:02,434
You can stay.
Just don't make me sorry I let you.

191
00:10:03,532 --> 00:10:04,441
Bassoon.

192
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:10,192
Mrs. Vickers, when was the last time
you spoke to your son?

193
00:10:12,186 --> 00:10:13,336
This morning.

194
00:10:13,518 --> 00:10:15,760
Selby always checks in on me
before he goes to work,

195
00:10:15,885 --> 00:10:17,709
to see how I'm doing.
He's...

196
00:10:18,894 --> 00:10:20,202
Was sweet like that.

197
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:23,288
Has he any problems?
Work? Personal life?

198
00:10:23,861 --> 00:10:25,588
No. Just the opposite.

199
00:10:25,882 --> 00:10:27,912
Things were starting
to get good for him.

200
00:10:28,037 --> 00:10:30,462
After he left high school,
things didn't go right for him.

201
00:10:31,086 --> 00:10:32,788
About high school.
The prank he pulled...

202
00:10:32,913 --> 00:10:34,466
I don't want to talk about that.

203
00:10:35,809 --> 00:10:38,209
His whole life was spoiled
by that...

204
00:10:38,509 --> 00:10:39,709
that incident.

205
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,350
He lost a chance at college.

206
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:45,015
He got stuck working
in a little print shop.

207
00:10:47,529 --> 00:10:49,379
And then Jana came along...

208
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:52,950
and she was like
a whole new world for him.

209
00:10:55,225 --> 00:10:56,675
She encouraged him,

210
00:10:57,323 --> 00:11:00,273
and she told him to strive
for something better.

211
00:11:01,552 --> 00:11:03,578
And he became a whole new person.

212
00:11:05,380 --> 00:11:08,680
We haven't been able to
track down any family for Jana.

213
00:11:09,034 --> 00:11:10,669
Do you know where we can find them?

214
00:11:13,614 --> 00:11:15,430
She didn't have anybody...

215
00:11:15,918 --> 00:11:19,011
Nobody that I know of.
She moved here from Poland,

216
00:11:19,694 --> 00:11:22,544
and Selby only met her
a couple of months ago.

217
00:11:23,097 --> 00:11:25,297
A few dates and they got married.

218
00:11:26,167 --> 00:11:28,255
It was all kind of a whirlwind.

219
00:11:30,129 --> 00:11:31,111
Mrs. Vickers,

220
00:11:31,236 --> 00:11:33,933
it's a bit unsettling, but I'd like you
to listen to this message,

221
00:11:34,058 --> 00:11:35,819
see if you recognize the caller.
Okay?

222
00:11:39,914 --> 00:11:42,332
<i>I'm done playing games here.
You hear me?</i>

223
00:11:42,582 --> 00:11:45,272
<i>Either you get me my money,
or I'm gonna be forced to take action.</i>

224
00:11:46,890 --> 00:11:49,286
I've never heard
that voice in my life.

225
00:11:49,522 --> 00:11:52,085
Was my son involved
with a loan shark or something?

226
00:11:52,419 --> 00:11:55,713
Could be. We traced the phone call
to a phone booth in galatin.

227
00:11:55,882 --> 00:11:58,759
- That doesn't really tell us...
- Galatin? That's where Jana's from.

228
00:12:00,461 --> 00:12:03,839
Selby met her there at a coffee shop
when he was on a delivery run.

229
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:07,067
Can you tell us anything about Jana
before she met Selby?

230
00:12:07,192 --> 00:12:09,061
Maybe names of friends,
where she worked?

231
00:12:09,971 --> 00:12:13,523
No, All that selby told me
was that things were tough for her.

232
00:12:14,759 --> 00:12:17,010
He didn't share any details,
probably

233
00:12:17,631 --> 00:12:20,345
because he didn't
want me making any judgments.

234
00:12:22,521 --> 00:12:26,075
You remember what we used to call you?
You were the frogman.

235
00:12:26,338 --> 00:12:28,330
Frog.
Because you played the french horn...

236
00:12:28,498 --> 00:12:30,412
- Yeah.
- No... And 'cause,

237
00:12:30,537 --> 00:12:33,075
you kind a sort a look like a frog,
but no offense.

238
00:12:33,343 --> 00:12:34,950
Yeah, no, I remember.

239
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,963
We used to get on you.

240
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:39,823
You know what?
I'm sorry about that, sincerely,

241
00:12:40,187 --> 00:12:42,089
but, what?
We were kids, right?

242
00:12:42,214 --> 00:12:45,347
- We were just kids.
- Forget it, forget it. I have.

243
00:12:46,151 --> 00:12:47,540
Dude, that time

