493
00:26:30,804 --> 00:26:32,339
These reunions are insufferable.

494
00:26:33,245 --> 00:26:35,364
What I wouldn't give
to be home on my couch,

495
00:26:35,691 --> 00:26:37,774
glass of wine, good book.

496
00:26:39,308 --> 00:26:42,301
I take it you heard about Selby Vickers
and his wife.

497
00:26:43,672 --> 00:26:45,368
That's... that's a tragedy.

498
00:26:46,381 --> 00:26:48,231
Selby was a truly good kid,

499
00:26:49,062 --> 00:26:51,120
until that one incident
with Derek Logan.

500
00:26:52,095 --> 00:26:54,245
Derek Logan was definitely
a different kind of duck.

501
00:26:54,370 --> 00:26:56,678
He wore the same tattered jacket,
be it hot or cold,

502
00:26:56,906 --> 00:26:59,098
always hugged the wall
as he walked down a hallway.

503
00:26:59,709 --> 00:27:00,656
He was off.

504
00:27:01,336 --> 00:27:03,344
"Off" isn't tolerated
in high school.

505
00:27:03,582 --> 00:27:06,896
Certainly not in the 30 years
I've been doing this job.

506
00:27:11,087 --> 00:27:13,458
Right over there is where
it all happened.

507
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:17,811
Derek's folks sent him to
a shrink afterwards...

508
00:27:18,230 --> 00:27:19,450
But it didn't help.

509
00:27:20,288 --> 00:27:22,317
A month later,
they pulled him out of school.

510
00:27:22,442 --> 00:27:24,289
That was the last I heard of him.

511
00:27:36,969 --> 00:27:39,094
Did Selby ever give
a reason why he did it?

512
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:40,956
You know, I asked him,

513
00:27:41,081 --> 00:27:44,286
but he just shrugged. You know, gave me
that teenage "i don't know."

514
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:51,558
How'd you catch him?

515
00:27:52,180 --> 00:27:54,087
- Derek was blindfolded, right?
- Yes.

516
00:27:54,276 --> 00:27:56,048
He heard
his attacker's voice, though.

517
00:27:56,943 --> 00:27:58,728
He thought it sounded like Selby.

518
00:27:59,519 --> 00:28:02,455
I confronted Selby.
He confessed quite readily, like the

519
00:28:02,805 --> 00:28:05,067
helpful, honest boy he usually was.

520
00:28:06,386 --> 00:28:07,543
It's very strange.

521
00:28:13,147 --> 00:28:15,010
You want me to memorize
everything we have

522
00:28:15,135 --> 00:28:17,520
on all 67 alumni
that showed up at the reunion?

523
00:28:17,739 --> 00:28:20,036
- Yes, I do.
- And how would I do that?

524
00:28:20,535 --> 00:28:22,825
It's easy.
You build a memory palace.

525
00:28:23,528 --> 00:28:26,504
- It was a card player's trick.
- Well, it's multipurpose.

526
00:28:26,629 --> 00:28:29,237
It's perfect for recalling
a large body of information.

527
00:28:29,362 --> 00:28:32,209
All you need is a physical
location that you know well,

528
00:28:32,643 --> 00:28:35,676
and you break it down
in your mind into smaller pieces

529
00:28:36,008 --> 00:28:37,440
and link each one

530
00:28:38,010 --> 00:28:40,307
to a package of the information,

531
00:28:41,025 --> 00:28:42,025
like this.

532
00:28:45,912 --> 00:28:47,496
I walk in the door,

533
00:28:48,558 --> 00:28:51,642
and I'm greeted by
reunion chair Willa Brock...

534
00:28:52,379 --> 00:28:54,982
Former class president,
debate team captain,

535
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:57,251
led the team to
three county championships,

536
00:28:57,555 --> 00:28:59,275
now a talk show host in Chicago.

537
00:28:59,933 --> 00:29:01,408
I sit down at the table

538
00:29:01,533 --> 00:29:04,387
and catch up with Dana Greer.
Swimmer,

539
00:29:04,700 --> 00:29:06,469
now a realtor in Los Angeles,

540
00:29:06,594 --> 00:29:08,805
married to a gentleman
by the name of Arthur.

541
00:29:08,930 --> 00:29:10,206
And so on and so forth.

542
00:29:11,977 --> 00:29:14,186
When you want
to remember the details,

543
00:29:14,635 --> 00:29:17,085
you close your eyes,
and in your mind,

544
00:29:18,213 --> 00:29:19,344
you walk around

545
00:29:19,469 --> 00:29:21,369
your very own memory palace.

546
00:29:23,566 --> 00:29:25,787
I can't learn all this
stuff in just a couple hours.

547
00:29:25,912 --> 00:29:28,007
It comes very quickly
once you get the hang of it,

548
00:29:28,132 --> 00:29:30,148
- and they'll be wearing nametags.
- But why?

549
00:29:30,273 --> 00:29:32,408
- Why would I memorize all these...
- It's fun.

550
00:29:34,017 --> 00:29:36,559
This is some dubious scheme
that Lisbon doesn't know about,

551
00:29:36,684 --> 00:29:38,109
You can count me out.

552
00:29:38,991 --> 00:29:40,277
Sorry, you gotta do it.

553
00:29:40,887 --> 00:29:41,863
No, I don't.

554
00:29:45,932 --> 00:29:47,526
If you don't cooperate,

555
00:29:47,651 --> 00:29:50,471
i'm gonna be forced to tell
Lisbon about you and Van Pelt.

556
00:29:50,596 --> 00:29:52,823
Tell what?
There's nothing to tell.

557
00:29:56,165 --> 00:29:57,104
Really?

558
00:29:57,538 --> 00:29:59,663
Yeah. I don't know
what you're talking about.

559
00:30:01,866 --> 00:30:04,792
Contrary to very strict
CBI rules and regulations,

560
00:30:04,917 --> 00:30:06,487
you and Grace Van Pelt

561
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:09,277
are engaged in an illicit affair.

562
00:30:10,696 --> 00:30:11,605
Nope.

563
00:30:12,402 --> 00:30:13,992
You're being childish.

564
00:30:16,185 --> 00:30:18,636
- Don't tell her. She'll report to HR.
- She's a stickler.

565
00:30:18,761 --> 00:30:21,390
- They'll throw one of us off the unit.
- Better get to work.

566
00:30:50,547 --> 00:30:52,908
School would be so much more fun
if they started the day

567
00:30:53,033 --> 00:30:56,168
with this every morning
instead of the pledge of allegiance.

568
00:30:56,293 --> 00:30:58,670
Or maybe they could
just integrate the two

569
00:30:58,795 --> 00:31:01,230
into the "dance of allegiance."

570
00:31:02,470 --> 00:31:05,091
We're taking a real flier here.
This better work.

571
00:31:05,216 --> 00:31:06,125
Timpani.

572
00:31:07,991 --> 00:31:09,742
Really got me stumped on that one.

573
00:31:10,131 --> 00:31:11,463
I'm just guessing now.

574
00:31:11,588 --> 00:31:14,224
We'd better get this thing going
before people start leaving.

575
00:31:14,349 --> 00:31:16,933
Patience.
The fun will commence shortly.

576
00:31:23,844 --> 00:31:25,152
Hey, how's it going?

577
00:31:26,231 --> 00:31:28,190
Nice to see you.
Long time.

578
00:31:33,459 --> 00:31:34,702
Coffee machine.

579
00:31:38,096 --> 00:31:39,246
Stu McAlpine?

580
00:31:39,996 --> 00:31:43,567
How goes it with my favorite
photo club president?

581
00:31:43,914 --> 00:31:47,162
- It goes great. How goes it with you?
- It goes whatever's better than great.

582
00:31:47,531 --> 00:31:48,821
I forgot your name.

583
00:31:49,593 --> 00:31:50,743
Well, it's...

584
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:52,850
Derek Logan.

585
00:31:57,512 --> 00:31:58,999
And it's great to be back.

586
00:32:05,606 --> 00:32:06,632
How are you?

587
00:32:14,089 --> 00:32:15,867
This is gonna be good.

588
00:32:16,667 --> 00:32:17,667
I promise.

589
00:32:19,576 --> 00:32:20,396


590
00:32:20,942 --> 00:32:22,469
Great to see you, too, man.

591
00:32:22,594 --> 00:32:25,502
Derek Logan.
I can't believe it.

592
00:32:25,627 --> 00:32:27,410
You've changed.
Who would've thought

593
00:32:27,535 --> 00:32:29,701
that the girl who brought
four schools to their knees

594
00:32:29,826 --> 00:32:32,585
in the high school county debate finals
would be lost for words?

595
00:32:32,710 --> 00:32:34,451
You just look so different.

596
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:38,007
Let's just chalk it up to 15 years'
worth of solid hours at the health club,

597
00:32:38,132 --> 00:32:40,103
plus maybe a little bit of work.

598
00:32:40,228 --> 00:32:42,162
You gotta look good
in my business, huh?

599
00:32:42,287 --> 00:32:45,165
Had to see
it to believe it. Derek Logan!

600
00:32:45,754 --> 00:32:46,925
L.J., hey!

601
00:32:47,476 --> 00:32:48,932
- Refrigerator.
- What?

602
00:32:49,057 --> 00:32:50,705
Rancho Rosa versus Stratton...

603
00:32:51,136 --> 00:32:53,783
The ball is on our 10,
2 seconds on the clock,

604
00:32:53,908 --> 00:32:55,785
sims hands it off, bam!

605
00:32:55,910 --> 00:32:58,221
You run 90 yards,
touchdown, toros win.

606
00:32:59,189 --> 00:33:01,542
You're half right.
That was against Deerfield.

607
00:33:01,667 --> 00:33:04,451
And it was a pass, not a handoff,
but it was close.

608
00:33:05,070 --> 00:33:07,451
Man!
That's Derek "freakin" Logan!

609
00:33:09,157 --> 00:33:11,167
I'm gonna make the rounds
to say some hellos,

610
00:33:11,292 --> 00:33:12,948
but it is great to see you guys!

611
00:33:19,255 --> 00:33:21,057
- You're a natural.
- I can't do this.

612
00:33:21,182 --> 00:33:23,587
You're doing it.
You ready for phase two?

613
00:33:23,712 --> 00:33:24,638
I can't.

614
00:33:25,095 --> 00:33:27,652
Think of it this way.
You mess up, we blow the case,

615
00:33:27,777 --> 00:33:28,985
and I tell Lisbon.

616
00:33:29,110 --> 00:33:30,758
You're a cold bastard,
you know that?

617
00:33:31,150 --> 00:33:32,593
Good evening, fellow Toros!

618
00:33:37,561 --> 00:33:40,320
Now is the part of the evening
you've all been waiting for,

619
00:33:40,744 --> 00:33:42,262
the achievement awards!

620
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:48,104
As voted by you,

621
00:33:48,229 --> 00:33:49,985
The 15th reunion class

622
00:33:50,198 --> 00:33:51,932
of Rancho Rosa High!

623
00:33:55,628 --> 00:33:56,729
Break a leg.

624
00:33:57,261 --> 00:33:58,648
Our first award,

625
00:33:58,913 --> 00:34:01,241
the "i can't believe
they're still together" award,

626
00:34:02,082 --> 00:34:04,676
- which goes to...
- Dave Mercer and Angie Diaz Mercer.

627
00:34:04,801 --> 00:34:07,044
No surprises there,
am I right, gang?

628
00:34:07,585 --> 00:34:10,422
- What are you doing?
- I'm let you finish, Willa.

629
00:34:10,590 --> 00:34:12,408
I just wanna say a few quick words.

630
00:34:12,831 --> 00:34:14,411
- Just make it fast.
- Sure.

631
00:34:14,536 --> 00:34:16,021
Slight change of schedule.

632
00:34:16,146 --> 00:34:18,771
We'll get right back to the awards,
but first,

633
00:34:18,896 --> 00:34:20,192
Derek Logan!

634
00:34:25,814 --> 00:34:28,244
I'm sure most of you
are scratching your heads,

635
00:34:28,369 --> 00:34:29,858
wondering why I'm here.

636
00:34:31,361 --> 00:34:33,361
I came here tonight because...

637
00:34:34,008 --> 00:34:36,664
I wanted to see how it felt like
to be here again.

638
00:34:36,789 --> 00:34:38,867
I'm not the same person
I was 15 years ago,

639
00:34:39,516 --> 00:34:41,995
so when I walked in
that front door tonight, it felt good.

640
00:34:44,368 --> 00:34:45,277
Thank you.

641
00:34:45,909 --> 00:34:46,818
But...

642
00:34:47,239 --> 00:34:49,739
as soon as I set my eyes
on you people,

643
00:34:50,463 --> 00:34:53,618
I remember how it felt
the last time I walked out that door,

644
00:34:53,743 --> 00:34:55,175
and I was that sad,

645
00:34:55,431 --> 00:34:56,881
defeated kid again.

646
00:34:57,792 --> 00:34:58,701
Sure,

647
00:34:58,886 --> 00:34:59,886
go ahead.

648
00:35:00,096 --> 00:35:01,496
Feel sorry for me.

649
00:35:01,662 --> 00:35:03,658
But you should also
feel sorry for Selby,

650
00:35:03,783 --> 00:35:05,644
may he rest in peace.

651
00:35:06,725 --> 00:35:08,063
About a month ago,

652
00:35:08,231 --> 00:35:09,443
Selby called me.

653
00:35:10,150 --> 00:35:12,612
He'd been trying to track me down
for months, he said.

654
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:15,154
He wanted to apologize

655
00:35:15,322 --> 00:35:17,022
and to tell the truth...

656
00:35:19,979 --> 00:35:21,979
The truth that never came out.

657
00:35:22,856 --> 00:35:24,856
You see, Selby was a follower,

658
00:35:25,263 --> 00:35:26,348
not a leader,

659
00:35:26,611 --> 00:35:28,188
and he did what he did because

660
00:35:28,313 --> 00:35:30,150
somebody else was there that day.

661
00:35:30,275 --> 00:35:32,004
Somebody told him to do
what he did to me.

662
00:35:32,172 --> 00:35:33,797
Yeah... That's right.

663
00:35:34,592 --> 00:35:36,144
Hey, Gina, what's up?

664
00:35:38,511 --> 00:35:40,111
He'll be fine. Just...

665
00:35:40,696 --> 00:35:42,196
Give him an aspirin.

666
00:35:43,254 --> 00:35:45,150
And I now know who it was.

667
00:35:45,850 --> 00:35:46,828
And that...

668
00:35:46,953 --> 00:35:48,903
is the real reason I am here.

669
00:35:49,237 --> 00:35:50,237
I am here

670
00:35:50,373 --> 00:35:52,065
to make you pay.

671
00:35:54,380 --> 00:35:55,830
You ruined my life,

672
00:35:56,887 --> 00:35:57,696
that day.

673
00:35:58,073 --> 00:36:00,282
And... I've spent 15 years

674
00:36:00,450 --> 00:36:02,910
struggling to get it back.
And now, I have.

675
00:36:03,930 --> 00:36:05,111
And I will have

676
00:36:05,236 --> 00:36:06,399
my revenge.

677
00:36:06,763 --> 00:36:07,672
Payback

678
00:36:07,797 --> 00:36:08,999
is a bitch,

679
00:36:09,504 --> 00:36:11,084
like in that movie with...

680
00:36:12,839 --> 00:36:15,390
Mel Gibson,
where they kidnap his child.

681
00:36:16,524 --> 00:36:18,724
Or is it the other one?
Anyhow...

682
00:36:19,014 --> 00:36:21,415
that's me.
Enjoy the rest of your evening.

683
00:36:21,540 --> 00:36:22,540
Go, Toros.

684
00:36:28,162 --> 00:36:31,157
- What do you think you're doing?
- The maid lent us this.

685
00:36:31,282 --> 00:36:33,582
You still should tip her.
It's the right thing to do.

686
00:36:33,707 --> 00:36:35,198
Must've been hard walking out

687
00:36:35,323 --> 00:36:37,923
in the middle
of a big event you planned.

688
00:36:38,141 --> 00:36:41,123
The speech was boring,
and I have to get back to Chicago.

689
00:36:41,248 --> 00:36:43,898
I have two shows
to prepare for on monday.

690
00:36:44,521 --> 00:36:46,721
I have a great idea for your show.

691
00:36:47,059 --> 00:36:50,259
"Humiliating pranks
and the people who initate them."

692
00:36:51,149 --> 00:36:53,049
You could be your own guest.

693
00:36:55,059 --> 00:36:56,725
You have no basis for that.

694
00:36:57,126 --> 00:36:59,840
I didn't want to have to hear Derek
go on and on about...

695
00:36:59,965 --> 00:37:02,415
Did your talk show
goes national soon?

696
00:37:03,192 --> 00:37:04,101
So?

697
00:37:04,530 --> 00:37:07,096
If Selby had gone to the media
with the story

698
00:37:07,221 --> 00:37:09,756
of how you brutalized
a helpless boy,

699
00:37:09,881 --> 00:37:12,377
your big chance would be history.

700
00:37:13,148 --> 00:37:16,398
So you arranged a meeting
with Selby to get the money.

701
00:37:17,181 --> 00:37:19,350
Jana showed up with him,
which you weren't expecting,

702
00:37:19,475 --> 00:37:21,175
so you killed them both.

703
00:37:22,468 --> 00:37:24,491
I didn't have to pay him
or kill him.

704
00:37:25,849 --> 00:37:29,749
Selby didn't have a stitch of proof
putting me in that locker room.

705
00:37:30,344 --> 00:37:33,000
The media would've ignored him
as a crackpot.

706
00:37:33,506 --> 00:37:35,656
"I have immortal longings in me."

707
00:37:37,345 --> 00:37:38,788
Do you remember that quote?

708
00:37:40,303 --> 00:37:41,653
It's Shakespeare.

709
00:37:42,605 --> 00:37:45,455
I think it was the quote
in my yearbook photo.

710
00:37:45,815 --> 00:37:47,065
And an apt one.

711
00:37:47,383 --> 00:37:49,349
High school was a wonderful time
for you.

712
00:37:50,357 --> 00:37:51,476
You could say that.

713
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:54,741
Star student, class president,
champion debater...

714
00:37:54,866 --> 00:37:57,042
You were at the top
of the social hierarchy.

715
00:37:57,167 --> 00:38:00,611
Willa Brock was the queen of the school.
Your world was perfect.

716
00:38:04,411 --> 00:38:07,001
But then something happened
and unsettled that perfect world.

717
00:38:07,126 --> 00:38:08,176
Derek Logan

718
00:38:08,943 --> 00:38:10,692
irked you, somehow.

719
00:38:12,194 --> 00:38:14,530
And you just couldn't let it pass
without a response,

720
00:38:14,655 --> 00:38:16,207
so you turned on the charm,

721
00:38:16,332 --> 00:38:19,120
you manipulated Selby
to do your bidding, knowing...

722
00:38:19,245 --> 00:38:21,315
that he'd be thrilled
to help the popular girl.

723
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:24,240
The girl he was always
a little in love with.

724
00:38:25,815 --> 00:38:27,957
And then you destroyed Derek Logan,

725
00:38:28,082 --> 00:38:30,032
to the delight of your peers.

726
00:38:30,491 --> 00:38:31,941
And you enjoyed it,

727
00:38:32,727 --> 00:38:35,002
'cause you found it all so easy

728
00:38:35,127 --> 00:38:37,688
and so empowering and exciting,

729
00:38:38,300 --> 00:38:39,209
right?

730
00:38:40,892 --> 00:38:42,923
All your success
at Rancho Rosa High...

731
00:38:43,378 --> 00:38:44,279
This...

732
00:38:45,324 --> 00:38:47,532
was Willa Brock's
crowning achievement.

733
00:38:58,106 --> 00:38:59,456
You've aged well.

734
00:39:01,868 --> 00:39:03,836
It looks like Selby
took more than one photo

735
00:39:03,961 --> 00:39:06,301
that day in the locker room,
didn't he?

736
00:39:06,679 --> 00:39:08,136
Have a look at that.

737
00:39:08,304 --> 00:39:09,554
Check that out.

738
00:39:34,917 --> 00:39:36,415
This is Selby's proof.

739
00:39:37,652 --> 00:39:39,873
But you didn't wanna pay him
all that money and risk him

740
00:39:39,998 --> 00:39:42,580
blackmailing you again,
so you killed him

741
00:39:42,755 --> 00:39:43,922
and his wife Jana.

742
00:39:47,618 --> 00:39:50,804
Kinda poetic,
how you were done in by your own vanity.

743
00:39:54,124 --> 00:39:55,354
Derek Logan

744
00:39:55,595 --> 00:39:57,728
told everyone I let him touch me...

745
00:39:58,280 --> 00:39:59,521
Like I ever would.

746
00:40:01,756 --> 00:40:03,650
I was deeply humiliated.

747
00:40:03,818 --> 00:40:05,468
So you ruined his life.

748
00:40:05,645 --> 00:40:08,408
And Selby and Jana Vickers
had to die, too.

749
00:40:08,805 --> 00:40:11,284
Selby falls
for that little polish girl

750
00:40:11,409 --> 00:40:13,259
and suddenly grows a spine?

751
00:40:15,193 --> 00:40:18,498
Things would have been perfect
if he just stayed lonely and pathetic.

752
00:40:21,595 --> 00:40:22,645
Close call.

753
00:40:22,979 --> 00:40:25,538
If she'd have destroyed
the negative that Selby had given her,

754
00:40:25,663 --> 00:40:28,669
- we'd have no evidence and no case.
- It was a trophy.

755
00:40:28,794 --> 00:40:31,430
It was a reminder
that the great W. Brock can crush anyone

756
00:40:31,555 --> 00:40:34,126
that dares stand in her way,
just like 15 years ago.

757
00:40:35,070 --> 00:40:37,670
Nobody advances an inch
from high school, you proved your point.

758
00:40:37,795 --> 00:40:39,644
Their instincts never change.

759
00:40:42,994 --> 00:40:44,900
Selby and Derek
would both be grateful.

760
00:40:45,068 --> 00:40:48,612
You two have an open invitation
if you want to join us at the 20th.

761
00:40:48,737 --> 00:40:50,637
Hopefully, we won't need to.

762
00:40:51,036 --> 00:40:52,836
Keep it in the dojo, Phil.

763
00:40:54,144 --> 00:40:55,474
One thing I don't get.

764
00:40:55,599 --> 00:40:58,340
How did you persuade Rigsby
to play this charade?

765
00:40:58,465 --> 00:41:01,846
I told him that you promised
to give him monday off.

766
00:41:02,529 --> 00:41:03,627
Not happening.

767
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:08,924
Well, that puts me
in an awkward position.

768
00:41:10,510 --> 00:41:12,267
I held up my end of the bargain.

769
00:41:13,500 --> 00:41:14,500
Oh, God.

770
00:41:14,708 --> 00:41:16,458
I used to love this song.

771
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:19,673
- Loved the song.
- I used to love this song.

772
00:41:19,798 --> 00:41:22,698
You love this song.
Obviously, you wanna dance.

773
00:41:23,579 --> 00:41:24,729
With you? No.

774
00:41:25,337 --> 00:41:28,724
Come on, you can pretend
that I'm that mean, cold-hearted guy

775
00:41:28,849 --> 00:41:31,446
that you used to worship from afar,
but never talked to.

776
00:41:36,933 --> 00:41:38,183
No funny stuff.

777
00:41:39,807 --> 00:41:40,773
Really?

778
00:41:56,426 --> 00:41:57,426
Trumpet?

